"```sql\nSELECT account.account_id\nFROM account\nJOIN client ON account.account_id = disp.account_id\nJOIN disp ON disp.client_id = client.client_id\nJOIN district ON client.district_id = district.district_id\nWHERE district.A3 = 'Prague'\nORDER BY account.date ASC\nLIMIT 1;\n```\n\nThis SQL query retrieves the account ID for the first client who opened an account in the Prague region. It joins the necessary tables using the foreign key relationships and filters the results to only include accounts associated with the Prague region. The results are ordered by the account creation date to ensure the first account is selected."